# CIA Triad Notes

## What is CIA Triad?

The CIA Triad is a core cybersecurity model based on:

* Confidentiality
* Integrity
* Availability

It helps protect information and systems.

---

## 1. Confidentiality

Protecting data from unauthorised access.
Only authorised users should access information.

## Examples

* Passwords
* Encryption
* MFA (Multi-Factor Authentication)
* Access control

## Threats

* Data breaches
* Phishing
* Insider attacks

---

# 2. Integrity
Ensuring data is accurate and unmodified.
Prevent unauthorized changes.

## Examples
* Hashing
* Checksums
* Digital signatures
* File permissions

## Threats

* Malware
* Data tampering
* SQL injection

---

# 3. Availability
Ensuring systems and data remain accessible.

Authorised users can access services when needed.

## Examples

* Backups
* Redundancy
* Load balancing
* Disaster recovery

## Threats

* DDoS attacks
* Hardware failure
* Ransomware

---

## CIA Triad Table

| Principle       | Purpose                  | Example    |
| --------------- | ------------------------ | ---------- |
| Confidentiality | Protect data access      | Encryption |
| Integrity       | Maintain accurate data   | Hashing    |
| Availability    | Ensure access to systems | Backups    |

---

## Real-World Examples

| Scenario                 | CIA Principle   |
| ------------------------ | --------------- |
| Bank password protection | Confidentiality |
| Detecting modified files | Integrity       |
| Website uptime           | Availability    |

---

## Importance of CIA Triad

* Foundation of cybersecurity
* Helps design secure systems
* Used in risk management
* Supports security policies

